SIMPLE: heavily
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heavily
<hw>Heav"i*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[From 2d
<er>Heavy</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a heavy manner; with great
weight; <as>as, to bear <ex>heavily</ex> on a thing; to be
<ex>heavily</ex> loaded.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Heavily</qex> interested in those schemes of emigration.</q>
<rj><qau>The Century.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>As if burdened with a great weight; slowly and
laboriously; with difficulty; hence, in a slow, difficult, or suffering
manner; sorrowfully.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And took off their chariot wheels, that they drave them
<qex>heavily</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Ex. xiv. 25.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Why looks your grace so <qex>heavily</qex> to-day?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Greatly; intensely; <as>as, <ex>heavily</ex>
involved in a plot; <ex>heavily</ex> invested in real
estate</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>In large quantity; <as>as, it rained
<ex>heavily</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heaviness</ent>⟦br⟧
